The paper deals with graph theory and optimization problems, specifically the k-Terminal Cut problem. This problem is related to graph cuts, which are often studied in computer science and discrete mathematics. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves numerical optimization, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA).
